  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDA Special Action Account</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">At the CIEC (Conference on International Economic Cooperation) in Paris in 1975-1977, donors committed 1 billion USD for the &#x201C;Special Action Programme&#x201D; (SAP) for the poorest developing countries. The programme was financed by the European Economic Community (EEC), the US and a number of other donors. In 1978, the EEC contributed 385 million USD, which were channeled to the developing countries through the World Bank&#x2019;s International Development Association (IDA). Denmark&#x2019;s share of this was 2.93 per cent - corresponding to approximately 70 million DKK. The loans were issued with a 10 year grace period and repayment over 50 years. Repayments from debtor countries are transferred to Danida through the IDA.</narrative>
  </description>
